[There has been local transmission of dengue viruses in northern Queensland after the viruses have been imported by viremic travelers from endemic countries. The risk of initiating a local outbreak following importation of chikungunya virus into these areas of Queensland where dengue virus transmission is occurring is real. In 2013, there were 13 documented imported cases of chikungunya virus infections diagnosed in Queensland (see ProMED-mail archive no. 20130929.1974825).

